SIMPLE: stilted
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Stilted
<hw>Stilt"ed</hw>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Elevated as if on stilts; hence,
pompous; bombastic; <as>as, a <ex>stilted</ex> style; <ex>stilted</ex>
declamation.</as></def> <-- also, formal or stiff; -- said of linguistic
style -->⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Stilted arch</b></col> <fld>(Arch.)</fld>, <cd>an arch in
which the springing line is some distance above the impost, the space
between being occupied by a vertical member, molded or ornamented, as a
continuation of the archivolt, intrados, etc.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Stiltify</ent>⟦br⟧
